org.processmining.plugins.cpnet.accesscpn.enginge.highlevel

Class CPNetSeededHighLevelSimulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • AdapterImpl
      • org.processmining.plugins.cpnet.accesscpn.enginge.highlevel.CPNetSeededHighLevelSimulator
  • Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public class CPNetSeededHighLevelSimulator
extends AdapterImpl
    Author:
    mw, svzelst @ 20151911: add random seed, remove the map of existing simulators svzelst@20151128: deprecated. The bindings returned by CPN Tools seem to be in arbitrary order. We can fix this upon creation of the bindings, however, for timed nets using some random delay, seeds will not work anyway, hence, we choose not to use seeds.

      • rebind

        public void rebind(Binding oldBinding,
          Binding newBinding)
            throws java.lang.Exception
        Deprecated. 
        Rebind a transition in another binding. Only output places are considered, i.e., it's as if the transition was executed in oldBinding and, during execution, after consuming all tokens (treating double arcs as test arcs), the binding was changed and tokens are produced in the new binding. This assumes the transition was just executed in oldBinding.
        Parameters:
        oldBinding -
        newBinding -
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
